O God the Father of mankind, who hast given unto me these {{name}}'s children, and committed them to {{gender1}} charge to bring them up for Thee, and to prepare them for eternal life: help {{name}} with Thy heavenly grace, that {{name}} may be able to fulfil this most sacred duty and stewardship. Teach {{name}} both what to give and what to withhold; when to reprove and when to forbear; make {{name}} to be gentle, yet firm; considerate and watchful.